#compdef lighthouse-parade
# =============================================================================
# lighthouse-parade — Cloud Four's "Node.js command line tool that
#                     crawls a domain and gathers lighthouse
#                     performance data for every page."  A site-wide
#                     Lighthouse audit runner that orchestrates:
#                       - Web-crawler discovery of all pages on a
#                         domain (respects robots.txt by default;
#                         honors path-glob include/exclude filters)
#                       - Per-URL Lighthouse audits run via Google's
#                         official lighthouse Node.js library
#                         (Chrome DevTools Protocol-driven)
#                       - Concurrent execution (default N-1 cores)
#                       - CSV aggregation of all Lighthouse scores
#                         (performance, accessibility, best-practices,
#                         SEO, PWA) per URL into a single report
#                     Designed for web-perf engineers who need to
#                     audit ENTIRE SITES (not just individual pages)
#                     against Lighthouse metrics.  Cloud Four is a
#                     well-known frontend-engineering consultancy
#                     (created 2007 in Portland, Oregon by Jason
#                     Grigsby and Aileen Jeffries; specialty in
#                     responsive design, performance, accessibility).
#
# Author:  Cloud Four contributors (@cloudfour) — Cloud Four is a
#          Portland-based frontend consultancy; Tyler Sticka, Jason
#          Grigsby, Caleb Eby, and others contributed to lighthouse-
#          parade.
# Source:  https://github.com/cloudfour/lighthouse-parade
# CLI:     src/cli.ts (uses lukeed/sade for argv parsing + lukeed/
#                       kleur for terminal coloring)
# Library: lukeed/kleur
#          ("The fastest Node.js library for formatting terminal
#           text with ANSI colors~!" — Luke Edwards' minimalist
#           chalk-replacement, designed for SPEED + ZERO DEPENDENCIES
